Class MachineSessionClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.codeteapot.jmibeans.session.MachineSessionClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MachineSessionFactory

    public class MachineSessionClient
extends Object
implements MachineSessionFactory
    Reference implementation of a MachineSessionFactory.

    It incorporates operations to create the credentials that will be necessary to successfully carry out the authentication processes when attempting to establish a session.

      • getSession

        public MachineSession getSession(InetAddress host,
                                 Integer port,
                                 String username,
                                 MachineSessionAuthentication authentication)
        Description copied from interface: MachineSessionFactory
        Gets a machine session at the given address and port, for the indicated user, as well as the authentication method used.

        The session created does not necessarily imply that the corresponding physical connection has been established. This method should always return an instance of a MachineSession implementation. Error handling is delegated to the implementation of the session methods, which have the possibility of throwing a MachineSessionException if they cannot be executed successfully.

        Specified by:
        getSession in interface MachineSessionFactory
        Parameters:
        host - Address of the machine on which the session is established.
        port - Port used to establish the session or null if using the default.
        username - Name of the user for whom the session is established.
        authentication - Method used to authenticate the user.
        Returns:
        The session for the given user on the specified machine.
